body:
I updated the basic components for the build.

---

@nelenkov Can you please state whether you are still using Eclipse with Ant to build the project or whether you migrated to Android Studio and Gradle?

I encountered this error with one of my apps: A comment without translation.
(see http://pastebin.com/ResJU1gT) 

I fixed it myself in JSONParser in a quick and dirty way:

line 467, replace :
String translationText = translation.getString("3");

with:
String translationText;
try{translationText = translation.getString("3");}
catch(JSONException e) {translationText = commentText;}

I do not know anything about GitHub so I can't propose a fix. Maybe one of you guys can do it?

This fixes an ArrayIndexOutOfBounds Exception, imho this change should be fine.

Also I updated opencsv 2.2-->2.3, import/export still works for me

@nelenkov can you review this and merge if this works for you?

API changed again :(

@fda77 do you know how to fix this (quickly?) @8p8web ?

